Welcome <%= @user.first_name %>, we are delighted to have you on board!

You've successfully joined our Computer Science Accelerator programme, and we look forward to guiding you on your journey to achieving your subject knowledge certificate.

This qualification is awarded by BCS, the Chartered Institute for IT, and accredited by the Royal Academy of Engineering, and can even set you on the path towards chartered status.

Now you're enrolled on the programme, you'll find all of the resources and support you need on your personal dashboard (<%= dashboard_url %>), including our handbook (http://ncce.io/csa-handbook), which will walk you through what to expect as you progress.

Next steps...

1. Complete our short questionnaire to assess your confidence and subject knowledge
2. Explore your personalised dashboard which shows you the learning pathway and courses we recommend you take
3. Complete a minimum of ten hours of CPD, which must include a face to face or remote course
4. Use our mock test to check what you've learnt
5. When you're ready, take and pass our test to receive your certificate

Funding

If you work in state-funded education, you may be eligible for a subsidy (https://teachcomputing.org/funding) to support supply cover for continuing professional development, paid to your school or college.

Get help from your local Computing Hub

